Solution to Challenges

Challenge 1 — Two Function Conflict

Create folder → git init → create team.py with greet() and farewell()
git add . → git commit → create GitHub repo → git remote add origin <url> → git push -u origin main
git checkout -b feature-update → modify both functions → git add . → git commit → git push -u origin feature-update
git checkout main → modify same functions differently → git add . → git commit
git merge feature-update → conflict appears → open team.py → remove markers → keep best of both
git add . → git commit -m "resolved" → git push origin main

Challenge 2 — Push Pull Vice Versa

Create folder → git init → create notes.txt → git add . → git commit → create GitHub repo → git remote add origin <url> → git push -u origin main
Go to GitHub → open notes.txt → click pencil icon → edit → commit directly on GitHub
Back in local terminal → git pull origin main
Open notes.txt locally → verify GitHub changes are now visible locally
